{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016Jc8uxCYXMHddENDiUh83w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The original configmap uses short-form DNS names:\n- `es-cluster-0.es-cluster` (instead of `es-cluster-0.es-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local`)\n\nThese work because Kubernetes pods by default have DNS search paths that include the pod's own namespace. So `es-cluster-0.es-cluster` will resolve to `es-cluster-0.es-cluster.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` because the pods are in the `elasticsearch` namespace.\n\nThe broken configmap uses fully-qualified domain names with the WRONG namespace (`default` instead of `elasticsearch`). These won't resolve correctly.\nI need to restore the ConfigMap to use the short-form DNS names, then delete the es-cluster-2 pod to force the StatefulSet to recreate it with the corrected configuration. I should verify how the configmap is mounted on the statefulset to understand whether the pod needs a restart for the changes to take effect.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":541,"cache_read_input_tokens":35402,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":541},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"782b539d-405b-4b15-b6ed-672a5555c97b","uuid":"e3c5a773-dd8f-4dd9-89d1-75fcf58855cc","request_id":"req_011CcMdJb9XkSEP1SWL6zJbt"}
